@page
@model elite_dangerous_colonise.Pages.PrivacyPolicyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
    ViewData["Description"] = "This page contains the ED Colonise Privacy Policy.";
    ViewData["url"] = "https://edcolonise.net/PrivacyPolicy";
}
<section class="mt-3 mb-3 w-full rounded-md bg-[#F0F0F0] pt-3 pr-5 pb-3 pl-5">
    <h1 class="p-1 text-center text-2xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">ED Colonise Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-l p-1 text-center text-[#0F0F0F] italic sm:text-left">Last Updated: 2025/12/10</p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">1. Introduction</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        This Privacy Policy outlines how ED Colonise (hereinafter referred to as "we", "us", or "our") handles
        your information when you use our website. Your privacy is important, and we are committed to being
        transparent about our data practices.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">ED Colonise collects the following information from users:</p>
    <ul class="ml-10 list-disc">
        <li>
            <b>Anonymous Report Data:</b> When you report a search result as "Locked" or "Claimed", we record
            this report to improve the quality of future search results for all users. This data is entirely
            anonymous and cannot be used to identify you.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Personal Blocklist:</b> To improve your experience, the search results you report get added to
            a personal blocklist that gets stored in two ways:
            <ul class="ml-5 list-disc">
                <li>
                    <b>Session Storage:</b> For your current visit (session), we keep a temporary list of
                    information to ensure the website functions correctly. This includes:
                    <ul class="ml-5 list-disc">
                        <li>Your personal blocklist of reported search results.</li>
                        <li>A timestamp of your last report to help prevent spam.</li>
                        <li>A flag to confirm you have passed the anti-spam check.</li>
                    </ul>
                    This information gets cleared when you close your browser.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>Local Storage:</b> To retain your personal blocklist for future visits, a list of your
                    reported search results gets saved to your browser's local storage. This allows us to
                    automatically load your personal blocklist the next time you visit ED Colonise.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Third-Party Game Data:</b> Our service is built on data from the game Elite Dangerous. This
            data is sourced from:
            <ul class="ml-5 list-disc">
                <li>
                    <b>Elite Dangerous Data Network (EDDN):</b> ED Colonise reads anonymised journal entries
                    sent by users who have opted into sharing their game data via EDDN.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <b>Data Dumps Provided by Spansh.co.uk:</b> ED Colonise processes daily data dumps provided
                    by Spansh.co.uk, which in turn sources its data from EDDN.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Analytics Data:</b> ED Colonise uses Simple Analytics to collect information about your visit to our website.
            This information is entirely anonymous and includes:
            <ul class="ml-5 list-disc">
                <li>The pages you have visited on our site</li>
                <li>The type of browser and operating system you are using</li>
                <li>The date and time of your visit</li>
                <li>The address of the website you came from (referring URL)</li>
            </ul>
            The full list of metrics and how they are handled can be found in their official 
            <a href="https://docs.simpleanalytics.com/what-we-collect" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">documentation</a>.
            Simple Analytics' collection and use of this data are governed by their own privacy policy.
            For more detailed information, we encourage you to review Simple Analytics' 
            <a href="https://docs.simpleanalytics.com/introduction-to-legal" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Data Collected by Our Web Host:</b> ED Colonise is hosted using a third-party web hosting service, Yema LTD.
            When you visit our website, Yema LTD may collect certain technical information.
            This information is standard for most web servers and includes:
            <ul class="ml-5 list-disc">
                <li>Your IP address</li>
                <li>The date and time of your visit</li>
                <li>The pages you have visited on our site</li>
            </ul>
            This data is collected for statistical purposes, to analyse trends, and maintain the security of our website.
            Yema LTD's collection and use of this data are governed by their own privacy policy.
            For more detailed information, we encourage you to review Yema LTD's
            <a href="https://www.winserve.co.uk/policies" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">Terms Of Service & Policies</a>.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">The information we collect from you is used in the following ways:</p>
    <ul class="ml-10 list-disc">
        <li>
            <b>To Improve Our Service:</b> We analyse your anonymous reports to understand which search results do
            not provide valid colonisation targets for the game Elite Dangerous.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>To Personalise Your Experience:</b> Your personal blocklist stored in your browser allows you to
            refine your search results by immediately removing search results you have reported from future
            searches.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>To Build and Keep Our Database Up to Date:</b> We utilise the data provided by Spansh.co.uk to create
            and update a database of star systems in the game Elite Dangerous. Additionally, we utilise "Docked"
            journal entries, sourced from EDDN, to keep our database fresh so that it more accurately reflects the
            current state of the Elite Dangerous galaxy.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">4. Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        We use sessions and local storage, which are standard web technologies, to store your personal blocklist on
        your device. These technologies are essential for the functionality of the personal blocklist feature. We do
        not use cookies or other technologies to track your activity across different websites.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">5. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        We do not personally collect, sell, rent, or trade any personally identifiable information with third parties
        for their own marketing purposes.
        <br /><br />
        However, we do rely on essential third-party services to operate and maintain our website. These providers may
        have access to or process specific data as part of their service to us. Our primary service providers are:
    </p>
    <ul class="ml-10 list-disc">
        <li>
            <b>Web Hosting:</b> Our website is hosted by Yema LTD.
            As described in section 2, Yema LTD collects technical data to provide its hosting service and ensure the security and performance of our website.
            We do not have direct control over this data collection. Their use of data is governed by Yema LTD's
            <a href="https://www.winserve.co.uk/policies" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">Terms Of Service & Policies</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Spam Protection:</b> To protect our service from automated spam, we use the Altcha CAPTCHA. Altcha is a
            privacy-respecting service that verifies you are a human by using a proof-of-work challenge, which does not
            require the collection of personal data, cookies, or user tracking.
        </li>
        <li>
            <b>Analytics:</b> As described in section 2, our website uses Simple Analytics to collect information about your visit to our website.
            Simple Analytics is a privacy-respecting service that collects anonymous analytical data without using cookies.
            Simple Analytics <b>does not</b> share this analytical data with advertisers.
            Their use of this data is governed by Simple Analytics' 
            <a href="https://docs.simpleanalytics.com/introduction-to-legal" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
    </ul>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">6. Your Choices and Control</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        You have control over the data stored on your device by our website. You can clear your personal blocklist at any
        time by clearing your browser's local storage. This action can typically be performed in your browser's "Settings"
        or "Privacy and Security" menu or by clearing your browser's history.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">7. Data Security</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        We take reasonable technical and administrative measures to protect the integrity of the anonymous data we collect
        and to secure our website. However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot
        guarantee its absolute security.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">8. Children's Privacy</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        Our service is not directed to individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect any information from
        children.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any
        changes. We will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy when we do so. We will also announce
        significant revisions on this website's official changelog on the
        <a href="https://forums.frontier.co.uk/threads/introducing-edcolonise-net-a-colonisation-candidate-finder.635882/" target="_blank" class="text-blue-800 underline">Fontier Forum</a>.
    </p>
    <h2 class="mt-3 p-1 text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0F0F0F] sm:text-left">10. Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="ml-5 p-1 text-[#0F0F0F]">
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please get in touch with us at <a href="mailto:edcolonise@gmail.com" class="text-blue-800 underline">edcolonise@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
</section>
